<div class="page">

  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>The Bitcoin Retirement</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">How does bitcoin support a retirement? Drag the sliders, watch the curves move, find your escape velocity.</p>
  </div>

  {% include 'components/tool-framing.njk' %}

  <!-- TAB NAV -->
  <div class="tab-nav">
    <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="question">The Question</button>
    <button class="tab-btn active" data-tab="calculator">The Calculator</button>
    <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="strategies">The Strategies</button>
    <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="math">The Math</button>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- TAB 1: THE QUESTION -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="tab-content" id="tab-question">
    <div class="construction-note">
      <p><strong>Coming soon.</strong> The framing essay for this tab — covering the three legitimate retirement questions and the strategy plurality posture — is in active development.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- TAB 2: THE CALCULATOR (active) -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="tab-content active" id="tab-calculator">

    <!-- CHART STATUS LINE — current price + Power Law context -->
    <div class="chart-status-line" id="chartStatusLine">
      <span class="status-prose"><strong>Today:</strong> <span id="statusPrice">$&mdash;</span> / BTC &mdash; sits at <strong><span id="statusRatio">&mdash;</span></strong> the Power Law trend; historically, BTC has been below this price <strong><span id="statusPercentile">&mdash;</span></strong> of the time.</span>
      <a href="/the-power-law.html#summary" class="powerlaw-link">What is the Power Law? &rarr;</a>
    </div>

    <!-- PROJECTION CHART — the workspace centerpiece -->
    <div class="projection">
      <div class="projection-header">
        <span class="projection-title" id="projectionTitle">Projected stack value</span>
        <div class="projection-legend">
          <div class="legend-item"><span class="swatch swatch-trend"></span>Trend (central case)</div>
          <div class="legend-item"><span class="swatch swatch-floor"></span>Floor band (conservative anchor)</div>
          <div class="legend-item"><span class="swatch swatch-upper"></span>Upper band (spikes)</div>
          <div class="legend-item"><span class="swatch swatch-stack"></span>Your stack (drawdown)</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="chart-wrapper">
        <canvas id="projectionChart"></canvas>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- LIVE EXPLORATION — slider clusters per §9.2.5 -->
    <div class="live-explore" id="liveExplore">
      <div class="live-explore-header">
        <span class="live-explore-label">Live exploration &mdash; drag any slider</span>
        <span class="live-explore-help">Watch the projected curve move as you adjust your scenario.</span>
      </div>

      <!-- TARGET CLUSTER (weightier register — what you want) -->
      <div class="slider-cluster cluster-target">
        <div class="cluster-label">
          <span class="cluster-label-main">Target outcomes</span>
          <span class="cluster-label-help">&mdash; explore your target annual retirement income and retirement year, and the trade-off between them.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="slider-grid grid-target">

          <div class="slider-control" data-key="targetIncomeUSD">
            <div class="slider-row">
              <span class="slider-name">Target annual retirement income
                <span class="help-tip" tabindex="0">?<span class="tip-content">Annual retirement income in today&rsquo;s dollars. Drag to explore: more income means the stack lasts fewer years; less income means it lasts longer or reaches escape velocity.</span></span>
              </span>
              <span class="slider-val" id="val-targetIncomeUSD">$100,000</span>
            </div>
            <input type="range" id="slider-targetIncomeUSD" min="20000" max="500000" step="5000" value="100000" aria-label="Target annual retirement income">
          </div>

          <div class="slider-control" data-key="retirementYear">
            <div class="slider-row">
              <span class="slider-name">Retirement year
                <span class="help-tip" tabindex="0">?<span class="tip-content">When retirement starts. Drag later to let the stack grow more before drawdown begins; earlier to retire sooner with a smaller stack.</span></span>
              </span>
              <span class="slider-val" id="val-retirementYear">2045</span>
            </div>
            <input type="range" id="slider-retirementYear" min="2026" max="2070" step="1" value="2045" aria-label="Retirement year">
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- INPUTS CLUSTER (standard register — how you get there) -->
      <div class="slider-cluster cluster-means">
        <div class="cluster-label">
          <span class="cluster-label-main">Inputs</span>
          <span class="cluster-label-help">&mdash; how you get there; the parameters you control</span>
        </div>
        <div class="slider-grid grid-means">

          <div class="slider-control" data-key="btcStack">
            <div class="slider-row">
              <span class="slider-name">Bitcoin stack
                <span class="help-tip" tabindex="0">?<span class="tip-content">Bitcoin held or planned. Drag to explore: how does the picture change at 0.5, 5, or 25 BTC?</span></span>
              </span>
              <span class="slider-val" id="val-btcStack">1.0 BTC</span>
            </div>
            <input type="range" id="slider-btcStack" min="0" max="50" step="0.1" value="1" aria-label="Bitcoin stack">
          </div>

          <div class="slider-control" data-key="withdrawalRatePct">
            <div class="slider-row">
              <span class="slider-name">Withdrawal rate
                <span class="help-tip" tabindex="0">?<span class="tip-content">Effective annual withdrawal as a percentage of your stack at retirement (in today&rsquo;s dollars). Coupled with target income: drag this and target income adjusts; drag target income and this adjusts.</span></span>
              </span>
              <span class="slider-val" id="val-withdrawalRatePct">6.0%</span>
            </div>
            <input type="range" id="slider-withdrawalRatePct" min="2" max="15" step="0.1" value="6" aria-label="Withdrawal rate">
          </div>

          <div class="slider-control" data-key="monthlyDcaUSD">
            <div class="slider-row">
              <span class="slider-name">Monthly DCA
                <span class="help-tip" tabindex="0">?<span class="tip-content">Dollar-cost averaging contribution per month between today and retirement. Each month adds BTC at the prevailing trend price.</span></span>
              </span>
              <span class="slider-val" id="val-monthlyDcaUSD">$0/mo</span>
            </div>
            <input type="range" id="slider-monthlyDcaUSD" min="0" max="5000" step="100" value="0" aria-label="Monthly dollar-cost averaging">
          </div>

          <div class="slider-control" data-key="yearsInRetirement">
            <div class="slider-row">
              <span class="slider-name">Years in retirement
                <span class="help-tip" tabindex="0">?<span class="tip-content">How long the stack needs to support your target income. Longer windows make depletion more likely at the same withdrawal rate.</span></span>
              </span>
              <span class="slider-val" id="val-yearsInRetirement">30 yrs</span>
            </div>
            <input type="range" id="slider-yearsInRetirement" min="10" max="50" step="1" value="30" aria-label="Years in retirement">
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- SUSTAINABILITY READOUT — §9.2.7 -->
    <div class="sustainability" id="sustainabilityCard">
      <div class="sustainability-header">
        <span class="sustainability-label">Sustainability</span>
      </div>
      <div class="sustainability-values">
        <div class="value-block">
          <div class="value-label">Years stack lasts</div>
          <div class="value-display" id="sustYearsLast">&mdash;</div>
        </div>
        <div class="value-block">
          <div class="value-label">Stack value at retirement
            <span class="help-tip" tabindex="0">?<span class="tip-content">In today&rsquo;s dollars (inflation-adjusted), the projected value of your stack the moment retirement begins &mdash; before drawdown.</span></span>
          </div>
          <div class="value-display" id="sustStackValue">&mdash;</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ESCAPE VELOCITY SPECTRUM BAR — §9.2.6 -->
      <div class="sustainability-spectrum">
        <div class="spectrum-track" id="spectrumTrack">
          <div class="spectrum-threshold-tick"></div>
          <div class="spectrum-marker" id="spectrumMarker" style="left: 50%"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="spectrum-labels">
          <span class="spectrum-label-left">Depleting</span>
          <span class="spectrum-label-mid">Threshold</span>
          <span class="spectrum-label-right">Escape velocity</span>
        </div>
        <div class="spectrum-detail" id="spectrumDetail">&mdash;</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- BASELINE ASSUMPTIONS — bordered cluster, expanded by default,
         with Hide affordance. Per RETIREMENT_CALCULATOR_DESIGN §9.2.9. -->
    <div class="baseline-cluster" id="baselineCluster">
      <div class="baseline-cluster-header">
        <span class="title">Baseline assumptions</span>
        <span class="help">Inflation rate &middot; Bitcoin growth model &middot; Traditional portfolio benchmark &mdash; adjust if you want to model a different world.</span>
        <a href="#" class="hide-link" id="baselineToggle">Hide</a>
      </div>

      <div class="baseline-cluster-body" id="baselineBody">

        <div class="picker-group">
          <div class="picker-label">Inflation rate <span class="help">&mdash; what's eating your purchasing power</span></div>
          <div class="picker cols-4" data-dim="inflation">
            <button type="button" class="picker-card" data-preset="cpi-official">
              <span class="val">3.5%</span>
              <span class="name">CPI Official</span>
            </button>
            <button type="button" class="picker-card" data-preset="m2-growth">
              <span class="val">6.5%</span>
              <span class="name">M2 growth (true inflation)</span>
            </button>
            <button type="button" class="picker-card" data-preset="shadow-stats">
              <span class="val">8%</span>
              <span class="name">Shadow Stats</span>
            </button>
            <button type="button" class="picker-card" data-preset="custom">
              <span class="val">Custom</span>
              <span class="name">Your own rate</span>
            </button>
          </div>
          <div class="custom-input-wrap" id="inflationCustomWrap" hidden>
            <label for="inflationCustom">Custom rate (%)</label>
            <input type="number" id="inflationCustom" min="-50" max="500" step="0.1" inputmode="decimal">
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="picker-group">
          <div class="picker-label">Bitcoin growth model <span class="help">&mdash; how price evolves over time</span></div>
          <div class="picker cols-3" data-dim="btcGrowthModel">
            <button type="button" class="picker-card" data-preset="powerlaw-floor">
              <span class="val">Power Law</span>
              <span class="name">Floor band (5th percentile)</span>
            </button>
            <button type="button" class="picker-card" data-preset="powerlaw-trend">
              <span class="val">Power Law</span>
              <span class="name">Trend line (default)</span>
            </button>
            <button type="button" class="picker-card" data-preset="linear-cagr-decay">
              <span class="val">Linear CAGR</span>
              <span class="name">With decay (secondary)</span>
            </button>
          </div>
          <a href="/the-power-law.html#summary" class="powerlaw-link">What is the Power Law? &rarr;</a>
        </div>

        <div class="picker-group">
          <div class="picker-label">Traditional portfolio benchmark <span class="help">&mdash; for comparison only; what your money would earn in a traditional 60/40 portfolio after inflation</span></div>
          <div class="picker cols-3" data-dim="realReturns">
            <button type="button" class="picker-card" data-preset="conservative">
              <span class="val">3% real</span>
              <span class="name">Conservative</span>
            </button>
            <button type="button" class="picker-card" data-preset="diversified">
              <span class="val">5% real</span>
              <span class="name">Diversified portfolio</span>
            </button>
            <button type="button" class="picker-card" data-preset="sp500-historical">
              <span class="val">7% real</span>
              <span class="name">S&amp;P 500 historical</span>
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="zone-footer">
          <span class="footer-text">Saved on this device only. Never transmitted.</span>
          <a href="#" class="reset-link" id="baselineReset">Reset baseline to defaults</a>
        </div>

      </div><!-- /.baseline-cluster-body -->
    </div><!-- /.baseline-cluster -->

  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- TAB 3: THE STRATEGIES -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="tab-content" id="tab-strategies">
    <div class="construction-note">
      <p><strong>Coming soon.</strong> The Strategies tab will frame the three retirement frameworks (sell as needed, borrow against your stack, disciplined rebalancing) as different shapes of risk rather than different reward levels.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

